	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b>Afew Thoughts and suggestions _ Making Healing More fun...</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Brenlo asked for some ideas to make healing more fun for raids...Okay...I've two ways off the bat, but they can be applied to both Shaman and Druids and mayhap even Necro/paladins.<br />
<br />
 I've other solutions too- most to making the cleric class more fun.<br />
 And one of our most emphasized issues that's been ignored, while other classes have risen  to fill the healing gaps when clerics were not avaialble or to substitute for us.<br />
<br />
 Clerics feel neglected and still hammered into the corner and told to shut up and make the game work for others at high end.<br />
<br />
 When not in high end combat, we should have other solutions for progression at least 80% as efficient as all other classes soloing. Hell at least 80% that of our sub class that at times can heal, buff, and dps better than us in any situation.<br />
<br />
 <br />
<br />
  Firsty ISSUE to Address- MAKING healing fun...in raids...<br />
<br />
   How to achieve this? Change it from the standard CH chain with someone spamming for DPS Burst AI changes...boring for 4-10 clerics depending on the raid or mob involved and insanely directed by another to fill in dps gaps from Rampages, bezerks, and untimely spell effects.<br />
<br />
   1a-  Healing battery...FOCUS BUFF!  Cast on MA and he becomes a font of healing. (increasing agro as if he were healing too)- His damage to the mob becomes by % of damage spread out to his group or in a pbaoe effect (covering other tanks in immediate area)  THIS means that the cleric doing the FOCUS BUFF is spending MANA to maintain this buff and via this buff transforms a percentage of that tanks damage into healing.<br />
<br />
 TANK (MAIN ASSIST) benifits by increasing agro two ways- via damage and taunts, and thirdly by being a PBAOE healer.<br />
  CLERIC can only maintain this spell for so long as it is a mana hog...the drain should be twice the best MANA REGEN AVAILABLE IN GAME! <br />
  This means per tick/rd that the tank swings dmg is totalled and then blasted point blank aoe radius as a heal (including himself in it). Each tick the spell drains more from the healer...if best mana regen were 45 Mana per tick the spells upkeep cost would be nearer to 100 mana per tick. Limiting how long that cleric could maintain this spell.<br />
   The spell would have another initial casting cost to set up the Heal Battery link. Suggest 1200 mana and start it at lvl 50 increasing percentage healed poing blank aoe by tank for each level of cleric doing it- THIS means JUST ONE BLOODY SPELL THAT GROWS WITH THE CLERIC!!! HAVING TO GET 5 different versions of the same spell as they level is one of the biggest plat and time sinks to a cleric and since they cannot solo well enough to get the cash themselves...its a big pain in the arse and a huge negative.<br />
  ANY damage to the cleric would require a channeling check (ie aoe's) if failed it BREAKS the link...requiring it to be recast. Moving or casting another spell would break this focus too.<br />
  That cleric does nothing but maintain the focus. Stress reduced...when mana's low for him he tells next cleric- Start NOW and breaks his focus when needed.<br />
<br />
    1a-b- Shaman and druids could get a different version that's a bit lesser in % return on damage done by main tank- or has a different result (ie procs a cure counter pbaoe every turn or a flare pbaoe based through the Main tank- these focuses could stack. So a tank could be blasting  pbaoe cures/heals/and flare bursts of fire/cold/disease etc every round. This increases their agro by leaps and bounds meaning clerics can fill heal, spam heal, and casters can nuke sooner...allowing more tatics to the end game and even to leveling. <br />
<br />
 How is this more fun? 1- Lessens pressure on secondary and chain healers by providing ways for tanks to maintain agro and to heal those near main targets. 2- Once focus is up and running, silence effects would have no effect on any link already established! Clerics not holding focus could spot heal and find other means of adding utility or dps to the event.<br />
 For druids and shaman- this gives them a non healing way of adding to the event. Meaning you can have more than one of each class in a group and they can be FOCUS casting and maintaining vs counting to 10 and pressing CH. Or counting to 3-4 and pressing CH after every cast..<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
 CONTINUED</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
