<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post221343"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Brodder</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">EQ's Beer God</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Dec 1999<br>
	Location: Hampton, Va. , USA<br>
	Posts: 453</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Continueing MAKING HEALING MORE FUN-<br />
<br />
<br />
 WE covered A battery of healing focus that drains mana from a cleric while changing some of the dps done by the main tank into a PBAOE heal every tick.<br />
<br />
 That's one way.<br />
<br />
 Second method-  EFFECT HEALS.<br />
<br />
  HIT YOU HURT YOU- Hit ME HEAL MY GROUP BUFF-<br />
  Not a Mini DS, not a Reverse damage shield BUT a SINGLE buff that breaks/cancels with one hit- no matter the damage to the cleric.<br />
  IT takes the damage done to cleric- converts it to heal (still hurts cleric before it goes off- so one shot kills on cleric can still fire spell, but the dead can't come back without rez).<br />
 This is a buffer spell- cleric get's hit for 3000 and it takes that damage and spreads it to group as needed...with a max of 30% to any one person upto that amount.... This is agroless heal.<br />
 So cleric in effect gets hit for 3000 heals max 900 hit pts with rest going to group as needed...if it's not needed it's wasted...<br />
 Spell can be chain cast on main healer to keep it up until MT can get the agro back or mob dies...<br />
 This isn't a damage reduction, this isn't a cleric heal, but a tranvergence buff that converts damage done to the cleric into a group heal by % until it's all used or not for his group.<br />
 This helps groups in small group (single) or two group raids especially LDON's where cleric might need a burst heal and having that buff up would help group vs aoe damage/dots etc.<br />
 This means a healer heals when he can't (ie is being summoned or plain ole getting beat on)...<br />
 Buff is short duration (5 minutes or so until cleric hits and breaks buff) easy to recast and keep casting too...but must be agroless heals or the cleric would never lose agro to the MT again until mob was dead.<br />
 So in effect a fast casting short duration buff with an effect that breaks it and fires off a % group heal spread to max in group of 30% to any one person- until heal is gone... from A to F (that's 6 in a group) down chart...so if cleric is number 6 on list and all heal is gone- well OOPS!.<br />
 This way two clerics can keep buff going on each other in times of agro and group still gets some healing, until MT get agro back or all in group except cleric's are healed.<br />
<br />
 The level requirements should be that this spell also is a LEARN ONCE and use REST of your CAREER...<br />
  Names- Martyr for the Faith- your taking damage heals group with no agro<<<-- emphasis on this.  NOT an AA, BUT a buff type.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
 Third- CONVERSION spell-  Changes Excess heals into damage channeled through the MT. LIFEFORCE HEAL Buff must be active...ie the PRE buff for this to work.<br />
 This means IF a TANK is damaged and healed to full the excess is converted into energy (Magic) that comes out on the very next hit by the tank into the main target. To prevent exploits of massive CH's converting to damage on the MT with little or no damage on him...this would require heals be over 1200 hit points and that at least 3/4 were converted to actual heal of real damage. AND that ONLY heals from that cleric that cast LIFEFORCE HEAL buff on MT could do this.<br />
 This means one cleric might be doing a FOCUS heal on the mt converting damage to pbaoe heals for himself and other tanks in area on the MOB, and another cleric might be doing lifeforce heals converting excess damage into magic damage on next hit by target.<br />
 A lifeforce heal buff (Links MT and cleric's healing only for that cleric and tank) cannot be up at same time as a focus spell by that cleric, but another cleric can carry the focus load while another does damage transvergence via his lifeforce heal link to that tank.<br />
<br />
<br />
  Converting excess heals and wasted mana into damage via the main tank, making him keep/build even more agro ? GREAT! That's more fun! Cleric not only is doing healing, but adding to DPS of the event via proxy of the main tank, making healing easier for all others at event. It's like hitting a mini LOTTO every few heals and timing it just right!<br />
  This would be the buff cast on the MT by the BURST HEALER for a event/instance/encounter or raid level encounter.<br />
<br />
 Again this could be limited to certain direct heal spells, and fast casting spells and keep CH out of the spells it can convert to limit max damage translated from the excess heals.<br />
<br />
 10 K Tank with the LINK up takes 9 K damage in a round A CH lands from a cleric in a CH chain healing 7500 of it. He's at 8500 hits...burst healer casts a 2k Heal....500 pts are normally in excess, but suddenly the LIFEFORCE heal buff translates this to damage-- 500 pts x X%  The X% based on cleric's level (not the spell- spell would be base lvl 40 and grow 4% per level from 10% burst damage to 60% or so adjust higher as excess heals should never really reach over 1000 since that would depend on a crit and damage done...capped at 3/4 the heal's power as excess...<br />
 So a 2400 heal burst with full crit could do 4800 theoretically, but the spell would tranverge only that amount over heal in excess- if the crit does cause the excess (ie 4000 of crit used to heal of a 2400 pt heal that'd leave 800 pt magic x max % by level to be popped next hit as excess converted damage... 800 is 20% of 4000 so it's under the 3/4 excess aegis- and it'd go through as a lucky Transvergence- YOU drew a straight flush! Hit the lotto! and the TANK gets a surprise on his next hit! BOOM! Big magical flare and damage spam...n more agro!<br />
<br />
 BURST excess heal damage would be immune from FOCUS heal font pbaoe damage as it's cast through not by or from a proc of the tank...<br />
<br />
  FUN?  HELL yeah! Help group and raid? Hell YEAH!<br />
  <br />
<br />
<br />
 ALL three of these solutions offer clerics a means to heal, heal mt and damage the mobs in different ways...vs the old ch chain.<br />
<br />
  Some are just different, some offer dps and agro maintenance to the tank, without overpowering tanks...<br />
<br />
 CONTINUED</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
