<!-- spacer --></td><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td></tr></table>
<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post221345"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Brodder</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">EQ's Beer God</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Dec 1999<br>
	Location: Hampton, Va. , USA<br>
	Posts: 453</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">None of the making healing more fun listed so far has addressed the issues of soloing for a cleric.<br />
 How to help clerics solo with out infringing on others?<br />
 Well who really gives a damn?<br />
  Clerics have had their healing, rezzing and buffing infringed on and been told to shut up and deal with it for 5 years.<br />
 Of course high end raiding clerics and bot clerics wouldn't feel the need anymore, but they surely have paid a heavy price and many are disillusioned and quitting.<br />
 2 clerics quitting in a high  end guild means DOOM for that guild more so than losing 2-3 casters or tanks or even both!. As this directly affects their high end raiding abilities as game is currently designed.<br />
 This creates a cascade effect in game, meaning more back flagging, stealing clerics from other guilds, BOTTTINg more clerics to fill in this gap.<br />
 This points out a major flaw in a game designed and balanced on one class.<br />
 Changes in healing and rez and other abilities have been enhanced in every class over the five years to make this disparity less of a burden on the whole of a guild to depend on clerics alone...BUT AGAIN this never solved the issues presented by clerics for over five years running.<br />
<br />
  THERE are gaps in healing and utility where lower healing with more utility are prefered for a group over a plain old max healing capeable cleric.<br />
 With this evident in game, it became the death of any cleric (mainly by perception as I am living proof that evoc clerics can live and prosper- on attitude alone if need be) who didn't focus his specialization in abjuration.<br />
<br />
 Issues to address here- are Give us full mitigation BY armor type worn vs by class. Armors/locations should have set damage absorbtions similar to that in DAOC and other games. <br />
 ARMOR doesn't care who wears it, it gets hit it stops damage or it doesn't period. You dodge/block/parry the damage or you don't, period.<br />
 Avoidance shouldn't be an issue with plate or chain wearers, it's heavy, and they will get hit more often, that's why they wear heavy armor. That's why clerics wear heavy plate- THEY HEAL they get agro fast and need the heavy stuff to stop a good portion of it so they can survive and heal themselves or others to win the day for their faith and friends...<br />
<br />
 This is a no brainer that really doesn't affect high end game, but means ALOT to the low to mid level cleric struggling to find a group and competing with other classes who can heal DPS cast magic, transport groups anywhere, and do it easier than they can.<br />
 This means a cleric soloing, should gain experince at a rate that's not TEDIOUS, nor Exasperating in comparison to druids and shaman who are PRIESTS TOO!<br />
<br />
  Clerics have been given an unlimited bowl of rice at the feast, while other classes slowly over time have been given steak, shrimp, and other delicacies to fill in the gaps...too much rice gets to be boring, sure yer full, but you don't get the same value per meal as others do, and therefor you struggle to get through a bland boring meal where others have fun, and enjoy variety.<br />
<br />
 Is it too late for the cleric? HELL NO!<br />
<br />
 BUT ADDRESS THIS ISSUE FROM THE BOTTOM UP- NOT THE TOP DOWN!<br />
 MAKE it easier for lower level clerics to SOLO and as their healing becomes more effective in groups and groups depend on them more at higher end game- lower that efficiency to solo.<br />
<br />
 Start at 90% effectiveness and move down to 50% (considering top end casting/melee dmg to be 40% with spells alone and not including OPTIONAL ABILITIES OR GEAR! <<--- IMPORTANT IN ANY BASE BALANCING!! You can tailor how AA's affect these abilities after the fact to allow for higher soloability as in lower levels or to allow clerics other means to solo- BUT THE BASE ABILITIES FOR A CLERIC shouldn't be balanced against healing, just leveling.<br />
<br />
 Figure out how much other PRIESTS can achieve mana wise per hour vs exps, and compare to clerics currently, (this is both melee and casting) Since druids and shaman get pets later and transform abilities to better their soloing and melee- clerics need the same benifits in a different form.<br />
 HERE IS WHERE YOU CAN GIVE DIFFERENT RACES AND DIFFERENT GOD CHOICES SOME DIVERGENCE- IF ONLY IN LOOKS OF SPELL WITH THE CASTER and not the effect.<br />
<br />
 Perhaps a cleric of Brell would get a sheath of earth/stone skin look for duration of such a melee based soloing spell, a cleric of innoruk might get a purplish glow about them, a cleric of bertox would look more decayed and undead...clerics of Mithrel Marr would get a Pink halo and glow...BUT what ever the spell did to enchance soloing at lower levels would be the same across the board...<br />
<br />
 Perhaps clerics if they got an unresistable stun proc on their weapons that proc'd often, they'd be able to solo better as this would stop a single round of attacks every proc, hence speeding up combat from their view, limiting need to heal themselves from damage taken, and having less mana to meditate back would mean more uptime for killing mobs.<br />
 This PROC buff would work well and as mobs leveled with cleric, the stun would get resisted more often by current game designs.<br />
<br />
 This is reverse mitigation and damage reciprocation not a real dps increase-- naturally reduced in power as the cleric levels...<br />
<br />
 One tool to help them. Might require they use their summoned weapons for this- so as better weapons become available to them as they level- they'd rely less on this buff/proc and their summoned hammers.<br />
<br />
<br />
 OFFER the clerics the ability to summon hammer and shield or 2h weapons as they level for soloing- these weapons would be tailored to the mobs they are supposed to be a bane too- Undead and more mobs that are undead types need to be actually ADDRESSED as undead- or need to enlarge the scope of what they should be the bane against- chaos/evil/unlife/etc...<br />
 sure evil clerics would wimper and whine, but they aren't necros or SK's and thus fall under the aegis of clericdom for good or bad.<br />
<br />
  These bane weapons can be flavored as you will. But clerics should not depend on mages for summoning holy weapons...<br />
 If changing what a cleric can summon is bad to the design- OFFER them Short duration buff that need recast nearly every battle when soloing that increase in effect vs designated mobs.<br />
<br />
  Make this buff mutually exclusive with higher end shared buffs in raids so that it's an either or on these buffs ifn gorups and raids, and cleric must choose to be offensively oriented at lower ability- yet still able to contribute to the raid, or focus on healing in the raid.<br />
<br />
 This  would mean cleric Buffs himself, pulls a mob casts YAULP and goes toe to toe...<br />
 Or casts buff and starts Nuking a specific mob type!<br />
<br />
 These buffs lower the absorb of the target to that cleric's damage ALONE !  so it's a solo tool for the most part.<br />
<br />
 Perhaps a TRANSFORM MAGIC buff- so all magic based spells cast now take on form of a different damage type, one that the mobs they can fight in area are more vulnerable to than just magic.<br />
 This buff would be short duration too, and make spells cost a wee bit more to cast, so that at higher levels this percent would be felt more and lead to more down time soloing, but NOT AS MUCH AS THEY CURRENTLY SUFFER!!!<br />
<br />
 There should be a transform BASE SPELL (lvl 5 spell useable through out career and one every 5 levels after) that changes magic to another type of damage for that spell-  COLD FIRE Disease....etc.<br />
<br />
 There should be different types of yaulp spells for clerics available as they level- one for melee exists right now, but a shout yaulp for casting (costing a wee bit more mana to cast faster, or doing more damage, or finding weakness taking more time and critting every cast...) This offers use of common spells they have in their library, while changing how they cast them.<br />
<br />
 A SURECAST ability granted at lvl 20- this is a 100% cast spell channeling ability at 120% cost of the spells mana-<br />
 You really need that ROOT to get off, that stun etc or that heal so you can live and escape or beat the mob? (Limited to exclude CH of course).<br />
 This refreshes every 2 minutes in game (Similar to quickcast in DAOC)- basically a cool down period...meaning it's emergency use and a base ability-<br />
 Other casters could benifit from this too.<br />
<br />
<br />
 DIVINE AURA's STOP ALL DAMAGE N SPELLS FROM AFFECTING CLERIC= 100 invulnerability...Okay...<br />
<br />
 OFFER clerics the option of training or learing a spell that buffs their absorbtion for the duration while lowering that of their target's...making casting or melee an easier proposition while not doing much to make them more effective in combat skill wise it does mean that any hits they manage to get off would do more as less would be absorbed by the target, and any hits they take would be lessened by that much too...Buff is cast on target like a Mark spell...but affects both cleric and target. SHORT DURATION therefore solo useable spell. As target could only have one such spell on it at a time.<br />
<br />
 This would be limited invulnerability- ie damage taken is lower for cleric and more for mob he's engaged with...but he can be hit and hit the target back with melee or magic or both.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
continued</font></p>
	
