<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post221347"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Brodder</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">EQ's Beer God</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Dec 1999<br>
	Location: Hampton, Va. , USA<br>
	Posts: 453</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">CLERICS need utility...but can't step on other classes while other classes can walk all over them...THIS has to end. IF only in perception initially in fact soon it must be redressed.<br />
<br />
<br />
 Many clerics don't want more damage or combat melee ability, but face the fact, over 50% of any soloing done by a cleric who can't find a group, or is grinding out AA's or farming cash for peridots, will be engaging in melee combat at some time in the event.<br />
<br />
 So what if the cleric can heal himself up to full with one spell. That takes mana too and mana takes time to regen.<br />
 Without AA's or good gear, a cleric is a slow moving easy to hit and kill target for even green yard trash mobs.<br />
 This means CR's are HELL for clerics who cannot defend themselves or move as fast or as unseen as others.<br />
<br />
 HOW can we redress this?<br />
 FOCUS MOVEMENT SPELLS!<br />
 What's that? SPELLS THAT COST MANA PER TICK TO KEEP UP BUT MAKE MOVING TO PLACES EASIER...<br />
<br />
 A PHASE SHIFT- GHOSTING- SPIRIT FORM- ANGELIC ETC form-<br />
  SHIFTING his MANA the CLERIC ripples the planes of reality about them becoming more etheral- this allows them to move slightly faster than normal-be mostly transparent (HUGE reduction in agro radius for mobs that see them) and making them fall slower thus taking near to no damage from falls...<br />
 IF they should run upto a mob and manage to gain agro- it'd swing cast at them and see it couldn't affect them and lose interest rapidly...<br />
 Bearer of these spells can have no outside buffs active except their own self buffs (or from charges/potions)...negating all movement spells except this one...<br />
 This would be a semi divine aura with speed, lower agro range (actual vs resistable), and ghost like form....They can't cast any spell except rez with a corpse targeted that' their own...but they can drag their own body to a safer spot...<br />
 Spell would have a set duration or cost X amounts of mana per tick making it's use tatical vs all encompassing...<br />
 Movement AA's and gear would enhance this upto and near sow levels but never exceeding them...<br />
 Duration would be in MINUTES vs seconds to allow for multiple zone runs to recover corpses...where graveyards are not an option and you're needed to rez a group you were with, or were soloing far from where others might be to help you.<br />
<br />
 This would exclude the need for clerics to ever get seperate utility spells and this is SELF ONLY with mana cost or mana maintenance while up. Making it a CR tool vs a tool for exploiting...<br />
<br />
 Baring this-  Create a token that a cleric summons himself and then once in same zone can click that will port him back to his corpse in Spriit form (INVUL zero agro radius) that allows him or her to move corpse to slightly safer location for a self rez and loot...this token places a buff on target that can be canceled at any time...but normally just when they need to rez or 60 seconds have passed...<br />
 EACh corpse can allow one token to be summoned and when corpse is rezzed token disappears or when it's used it disappears and cleric ports into zone back to corpse...<br />
<br />
 This too removes need of invis and utility speed type spells...allowing for ease of self CR's and eventually group CR's and rezzes... TOKEN would also have LOC and zone name of where you died so in case you had to log after death you'd have a lil reminder when you delved the summoned corpse token...<br />
<br />
<br />
 MORE LATER tis 3 am and I need sleep....<img src="../ubb/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
	
