<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post221522"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Reorx</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Dec 1999<br>
	Location: Toronto, Canada<br>
	Posts: 53</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Those are all great ideas...would love to see some/all be implemented in some form, but the problem is whether or not SOE wishes to add new design elements to the game. The way I see it is cleric's abilities (and most classes really) haven't changed much in the last 5 years. In the original game we could heal, buff, rez, nuke some, melee badly. 5 years later we heal better (or less with CH!), buff better rez better, nuke slightly better, melee a little better...no fundamental changes, no new abilities or major design changes. The only thing major thing I can think of is Divine Arbritration which is a great AA. Second to that might be our reverse damage shields which only have limited uses. <br />
<br />
Of course, maybe I'm wrong about this, but I'm sure we've all seen some great ideas over the years that went in the abyss where all EQ ideas have seem to have gone. While I'm slightly optimistic about the recent communication with the devs, I'm holding out until I actually see whether they can, or will, break out of the existing design bubbles. I mean if they are 'stuck' thinking that clerics can only heal/rez/buff/nuke bad/melee bad then any future improvements will be similarily 'stuck' around these elements. Most of the suggestions brought up on this and other cleric boards, however, lie outside this with the exception of raid healing problems which goes beyond just cleric balancing.<br />
<br />
Overall I'm taking a pessimistic wait and see approach...it seems the devs want to improve the game but how well this will translate into the actual game, only time will tell.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Reorx Holybeard<br />
Level 65 (30 AA) Dwarven Cleric of Brell, Lord of Unrest, Bane of the Undead, Biter of Shins, Drinker of Ale (not nessecarily in that order)<br />
Tunare Server</font></p></p>
